
                                            Cape Town Mayor, Patricia De Lille says they have asked tourists and spectators to save water. 
                                         CAPE TOWN - Fans of Sevens Rugby  can look forward to a jam-packed weekend of rugby on Saturday and Sunday. Earlier this year, tickets for both days sold out in less than two hours. Cape Town Mayor, Patricia De Lille  says they have asked tourists and spectators to save water.  “We, of course, sensitised all supporters about saving water. We have already put out water measure in place. In the bathrooms, you will see there will be signs up all over.”